<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>74382</id>
	<title>EDITING: Let Format &gt; Character... apply to a drawing textbox to affect all text within the box</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">1 Create a new document in Writer.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">2 On the Drawing toolbar, click the Text button.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">3 Draw a textbox in the document.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.4">4 Enter some text into the textbox.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.5">5 Click outside the textbox to deselect it.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.6">6 Click the textbox to select it.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.7">As expected, it is no longer in the text-editing mode that was in effect in step 4.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.8">7 Issue:  The Format &gt; Character... option in the main menu is greyed out.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.9">If this option were available, it would allow changing all text in the textbox immediately.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.10">8 To work around this issue, the user needs to double-click the textbox to turn on text-editing mode, then Select All of the text before selecting Format &gt; Character...</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">This issue probably applies to other menu options also, such as Format &gt; Paragraph...</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">LibreOffice 4.1.4.2 on Ubuntu 13.04.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
